Planned Features
----------------

 o Content negotiation:
   * Accept: header handling
   * Output filter plugin framework
   * Metadata extraction plugin framework 

 o Metadata REST API:
   * /search - Find resources via metadata search
   * /metadata - Fetch/query metadata

 o Admin handler framework

 o Authentication/Authorization

 o More featureful backends
   * RDF metastore
   * High-performance filestore 

 o Utility scripts for switching filestores, metastores, mass-updates of 
   metadata, etc. 

 o Pretty jQuery+Ext-enabled interface
   * Search forms
   * Metadata grid view
   * Result galleries

 o Aggregate fetch
   * /metadata/«uuid1»,«uuid2»,«uuidn»
       * Maybe POST a list of uuids for metadata fetching
   * /«uuid1»,«uuid2»,«uuidn»

Do me straight away
-------------------

- Metastore value format -- object/string serialization (use YAML's #taguri ?) 

- Client -- use content disposition filename if none is specified, fallback to using
  mime type mappings in constants

- Write a benchmarking suite so we can establish a baseline of performance and track the impact on
  performance of any future changes.
  * AutoBench? (http://www.xenoclast.org/autobench/)
  * Httperf? (http://www.hpl.hp.com/research/linux/httperf/)
  * 'ab' with gnuplot output?

- Update docs!  Fill in placeholders now that APIs are solid.

- Handle the HTTP::NOT_ACCEPTABLE case; currently this 404s if the body is set, but the status
  is still the default.

- PUT/POST /metadata to upload metadata key/values pairs en masse.

- Metadata transaction block

- Spoolfile upload cleanup?

- HTML header/footer wrapping, with optional HEAD injection


Metastore search interface notes:
---------------------------------
exact        ( :find_by_exact_property )
pattern      ( :find_by_matching_property )
exist checks ( :find_by_exact_key )
             ( :find_by_matching_key )
type-specific 
	- date operations ( :before, :after, :during )
	  ( :find_by_date_property )
	- numeric operations ( >, <, % )
	  ( :find_by_numeric_property )
	- set operations ( intersection, union, difference, exclusion )
	  ( :find_by_membership_property )
	

